This code intends to negate a `Vec2` and print the result, but it prints the wrong output. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
struct Vec2 {
    int x{}; int y{};
    Vec2 operator-() const { return *this; }
};
int main() {
    Vec2 v{ 3, -7 };
    Vec2 w = -v;
    std::cout << w.x << ' ' << w.y << '\n';
}
```
